<subSubSection id="C30A6567FFA6F732FF026A3EFE70E626" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="18" pageNumber="525" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFA6F733FF026A3EFEC3E1EF" blockId="18.[144,759,1299,1412]" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFA6F733FF026A3EFEC7E143" box="[144,262,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The nominal subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFA6F733FDC16A3EFD70E143" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[595,689,1299,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virgo">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFA6F733FDC16A3EFD70E143" box="[595,689,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">G. virgo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
averages slightly smaller, with less intensely coloured hindwings than 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D6FFFA6F733FECE6A7DFE15E10D" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="2009" box="[348,468,1360,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Grammia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="virgo" subSpecies="gigas">
ssp. 
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFA6F733FE0A6A7CFE15E10D" box="[408,468,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, (male forewing length 
<quantity id="4CE89B09FFA6F733FF026A42FF34E1EF" box="[144,245,1391,1412]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2199999999999998" pageId="18" pageNumber="525" unit="mm" value="22.2">22.2 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFA6F733FF026A9DFEDBE22B" blockId="18.[144,759,1456,1600]" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="B964EAFEFFA6F733FF026A9DFEE0E1AE" box="[144,289,1456,1477]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">Distribution:</emphasis>
The nominate subspecies occurs from the Great Lakes region and Atlantic seaboard south through New 
<collectingCountry id="F307767CFFA6F733FEAD6AC0FE63E268" box="[319,418,1517,1539]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">England</collectingCountry>
, to at least West Virginia. Boreal populations (Fig. 8C) occur west to northeastern BC.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAF36ECFFA6F733FF516954FD02E2E5" blockId="18.[195,707,1657,1711]" box="[195,707,1657,1678]" pageId="18" pageNumber="525">
